The text leads to mate.  Black's alternatives are 26. ... Kh8? losing to Qxf7 and mate to follow.  If 26. ... Kf8 then 27. Rxh7 is winning; e.g. 27. ... Rxh7  28. Rxh7 Nd8  29. Qf6+ and mate to follow.  If 26. ... Rg7 then 27. Qxe6+ (27. ...Kh8?? 28. Qe8+ Rg8  29. Rxh7#) also ( 27. ...Rf7 is met with Rxh7 with mate to follow) and so Black's best try is perhaps 27. ... Kf8 but White's material advantage of two pawns and an exchange will win
